Instructor of record for Biol 0380: The Ecology and Evolution of Infectious Diseases. Course enrollment is 80 students.

Course Learning Objectives
Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to:
* Describe the biology of numerous infectious diseases, such as COVID-19, malaria, HIV/AIDS, and the plague
* Apply the fundamentals of current ecological and evolutionary theory to infectious microbes and their hosts, with particular emphasis on epidemiology, population genetics, host/pathogen coevolution and zoonoses.
* Examine, interpret, and synthesize the peer-reviewed scientific literature.
* Create an original research poster that explores a pressing issue in the public health sphere over the course of the semester using concepts from class as well as ideas from other disciplines
